# Welcome to My Basecamp 1
Welcome to My Basecamp 1

## Task
You will have a to create a website which mimique features from the original tools My Basecamp. It means having a database, a backend and a frontend.
This project is splitted in 3 parts.

We want our users to create their accounts, to connect and create projects!

As developer you need to think about the User Experience and it needs to be great.

## Description

- This is a project meant to facilitate project management amoungst a team

- The Main functionalities are:
  - A user can Register
  - A user can to perform CRUD on a project
  - A user can be added, deleted edited or viewed. Note only admin has permission to delete, view and edit all users unless it is the user editing his account himself
  - User should have a role either a simple user or a user and an admin at the same time.
  - A user who created the project is the project admin and can:
      * Add or remove an attachment from the project
      * Associate or remove another user from his project
      * Creat, edit, delete a thread or conversation for his project
      * write messages in the project conversation channel
  - Only users associated with the project can wite messages in the thread
  - Only the owner of a project can edit or delete a project except the      admin.
  - when session is expired the user is redirected to the login page.

# Project Structure for the API 

- The project is structured as follows:
    -src : contains themain source code of the frontend of our project
        - components : contains some react components for our project
        - constants : contains some constants for our project
        - context : for state handling of the various entities of our project
        - routes : contains some routes of our project
        - services : contains some services which have the various methods for carrying out request to the backend server
        - utils : contains some reusable functions in our code
        - views : contains methods the render our html pages
        


